<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,152,1737]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1071,1097]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Etymology:</emphasis>
Combination of 
<taxonomicName box="[546,668,1072,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,668,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trichillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1868" box="[728,866,1072,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pedaridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[728,866,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pedaridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the fact that species included have been originally described in these different genera. This name was also found in some of A. Martínez's identification labels. Gender neutral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,152,1737]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,1191,1217]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Distribution:</emphasis>
Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[482,602,1192,1218]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
to Central 
<collectingCountry box="[733,852,1192,1218]" name="Argentina" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, absent in Western Amazonia, Central and Northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[243,318,1232,1258]" name="Brazil" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Exhibits disjunct distribution comprising southern Mesoamerican dominion (Eastern Central America and Western Panamanian Isthmus provinces) and Choco and Western 
<collectingCountry box="[1096,1193,1272,1298]" name="Ecuador" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
provinces in Northwestern South American dominion, in the Caribbean subregion; Amapa and southern Pantanal provinces in the Amazonian subregion; Chaco and Pampa provinces in Chacoan subregion, and Parana Forest in Parana subregion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,152,1737]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,1431,1457]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks:</emphasis>
This genus is undoubtedly related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[783,965,1432,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Bradypodidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[783,965,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Bradypodidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(q.v.), and is defined by the following apomorphies: projection of lateral part of gena; convexity of head disc, and shallow concavities anterior to the eyes. This genus has very variable parameral shapes (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[837,934,1512,1538]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–94" captionStartId="65.[151,269,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[210,1372,194,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-48@65.[210,1372,194,1938]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 87–94. 87. Pedaridium hirsutum, pronotum; 88–90: Pereiraidium almeidai: 88. ♂ head; 89. parameres; 90. ♀ head; 91–92: Silvinha unica: 91. head; 92. parameres; 93–94: Trichillidium quadridens: 93. head; 94. parameres." pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Figs. 94</figureCitation>
, 96).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,152,1737]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,367,1551,1577]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Composition:</emphasis>
Apart of the 
<typeStatus box="[530,580,1552,1578]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
species, this genus includes 
<taxonomicName authority="(Howden &amp; Young, 1981)" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName=": Howden &amp; Young" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[925,1431,1552,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevisetosum" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[925,1108,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">T. brevisetosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Howden, H. F. &amp; Young, O. P." box="[1125,1422,1552,1578]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref48888" refString="Howden, H. F. &amp; Young, O. P. (1981) Panamanian Scarabaeinae: taxonomy, distribution, and habits (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae). Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 18 (1), 1 - 173." type="journal article" year="1981">Howden &amp; Young, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,366,1591,1617]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,366,1591,1617]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1868" box="[540,678,1592,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pedaridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[540,678,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pedaridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Martinez, 1974)" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName=": Ferreira &amp; Galileo" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[705,1042,1592,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caingua" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[705,829,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">T. caingua</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez, A." box="[847,1032,1592,1618]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="65 - 68" refId="ref49730" refString="Martinez, A. (1974) Una nueva especie de Ateuchina (Col. Scarabaeidae, Coprini). Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 197 (4 - 6), 65 - 68." type="journal article" year="1974">Martínez, 1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1055,1271,1591,1617]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1055,1271,1591,1617]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,289,1632,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pedaridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Pedaridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a question mark), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Robinson, 1948)" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName=": Howden &amp; Young" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[567,903,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosum" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[567,691,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">T. pilosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson, M." box="[703,894,1632,1658]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="35 - 36" refId="ref50759" refString="Robinson, M. (1948) Two new species of Neotropical Scarabaeidae (Coleoptera). Entomological News, 59, 35 - 36." type="journal article" year="1948">Robinson, 1948</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[915,1128,1631,1657]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[915,1128,1631,1657]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(described as 
<taxonomicName box="[1297,1419,1632,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1297,1419,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trichillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and at least one or two species yet undescribed.
</paragraph>
